A012003.name: E.g.f. cos(log(cos(x))), even powers only.
formula: For n>1, a(n) appears to be divisible by 3, and the highest exponent of 2 in a(2m+1) seems to be A001511(m). - _Ralf Stephan_, Aug 14 2013

A012007.name: cosh(log(cos(x))) = 1+3/4!*x^4+30/6!*x^6+693/8!*x^8+25260/10!*x^10...
formula: a(n) = (1/2)*((-1)^n+A000364(n)). Also cosh(log(cos(x))) = 1/2*(cos(x)+1/cos(x)) is the reciprocal of the e.g.f. of A012009. - _Peter Bala_, Dec 02 2011

A012009.name: sech(log(cos(x)))=1-3/4!*x^4-30/6!*x^6-63/8!*x^8+12540/10!*x^10...
formula: E.g.f. sech(log(cos(x)) = 2*cos(x)/(1+cos^2(x)) is the reciprocal of the e.g.f. of A012007. - Peter Bala, Dec 02 2011

A012019.name: E.g.f.: exp(sin(arctan(x))).
formula: Limit n->infinity a(n)/(2*n^(n-1/3)*exp(3/4*n^(1/3)-n)/sqrt(3)) - cos(3/4*sqrt(3)*n^(1/3) + Pi/6 - Pi/2*mod(n,4)) = 0. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 09 2013

A012020.name: Expansion of e.g.f.: sin(sin(arctan(x))) (odd powers only).

A012021.name: Expansion of e.g.f.: tan(sin(arctan(x))) (odd powers only).

A012022.name: Expansion of e.g.f.: arctan(sin(arctan(x))) (odd powers only).

A012024.name: E.g.f. sinh(sin(arctan(x))) (odd powers only).
formula: Lim sup n->infinity |a(n)|/(2^(2*n+5/3) * exp(3/4*(2*n)^(1/3)-2*n) * n^(2*n+2/3) / sqrt(3)) = 1. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 09 2013

A012025.name: E.g.f. arcsinh(sin(arctan(x))) = arcsinh(x/(1+x^2)^(1/2)) (odd powers only).
formula: arcsinh(x/(1+x^2)^(1/2)) = x/sqrt(1+x^2)*(1 - x^2/(G(0)+x^2)) where G(k) = 4*k^2 + k*(10+6*x^2) + 5*x^2 + 6 + 2*x^2*(1+x^2)*(k+1)*(2*k+3)^3/G(k+1) ; (continued fraction, Euler's 1st kind, 1-step). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Aug 08 2012

A012026.name: Expansion of e.g.f. tanh(sin(arctan(x))) = tanh(x/sqrt(1+x^2)) (odd powers only).
formula: E.g.f.: tanh(x/sqrt(1+x^2)) = (x/sqrt(1+x^2))*G(0) where G(k)=  1 - x^2/(x^2 + (1+x^2)*(2*k+1)*(2*k+3)/G(k+1)); (continued fraction, 2-step). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Aug 06 2012

A012027.name: E.g.f. cosh(sin(arctan(x))) = cosh(x/sqrt(1+x^2)) (even powers only).
formula: E.g.f.: cosh(x/sqrt(1+x^2)) = 1 + x^2/(G(0) - x^2) where G(k)= (2*k+2)*(2*k+1)*(1+x^2) + x^2 - (2*k+2)*(2*k+1)*x^2*(1+x^2)/G(k+1); (continued fraction, Euler's kind, 1-step). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Aug 06 2012
Lim sup n->infinity |a(n)|/(2^(2*n+2/3) * exp(3/4*(2*n)^(1/3)-2*n) * n^(2*n-1/3) / sqrt(3)) = 1. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 09 2013

A012028.name: E.g.f. sec(sin(arctan(x))) = 1/cos(x/sqrt(1+x^2)).
formula: E.g.f.: 1/cos(x/sqrt(1+x^2)) = 1 + x^2/(G(0)) where G(k)= 2*(2*k+1)*(k+1)*(1+x^2) - x^2 + 2*(2*k+1)*(k+1)*x^2*(1+x^2)/G(k+1); (continued fraction, Euler's 1st kind, 1-step). - Sergei N. Gladkovskii, Aug 06 2012

A012034.name: exp(sin(arcsinh(x))) = 1+x+1/2!*x^2-1/3!*x^3-7/4!*x^4+1/5!*x^5...
formula: a(n) ~ 2 * n^(n-1) * cosh(Pi/2) * sin(Pi*n/2-sinh(Pi/2)) / exp(n). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 30 2013

A012035.name: sin(sin(arcsinh(x))) = x-3/3!*x^3+41/5!*x^5-1291/7!*x^7+73169/9!*x^9...
formula: a(n) ~ (-1)^n * 2^(2*n+1) * n^(2*n) * cosh(sinh(Pi/2)) * cosh(Pi/2) / exp(2*n). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 30 2013

A012039.name: sinh(sin(arcsinh(x))) = x-1/3!*x^3+1/5!*x^5+111/7!*x^7-9407/9!*x^9...
formula: a(n) ~ (-1)^n * cos(sinh(Pi/2)) * cosh(Pi/2) * 2^(2*n+1) * n^(2*n) / exp(2*n). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 30 2013

A012043.name: cosh(sin(arcsinh(x))) = 1+1/2!*x^2-7/4!*x^4+121/6!*x^6-4271/8!*x^8...
formula: a(n) ~ (-1)^(n+1) * sin(sinh(Pi/2)) * cosh(Pi/2) * 2^(2*n) * n^(2*n-1) / exp(2*n). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 30 2013

A012077.name: tan(arcsin(tan(x))) = x+5/3!*x^3+121/5!*x^5+6845/7!*x^7+698161/9!*x^9...
formula: a(n) = Sum_(m=0..n, binomial(2*m,m)*Sum_(j=0..2*n-2*m, binomial(j+2*m,2*m)*(j+2*m+1)!*2^(2*n-j-4*m)*(-1)^(n+m+j)*stirling2(2*n+1,j+2*m+1))) /((2*n+1)!), n>0. - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Jun 15 2011

A012079.name: cos(arcsin(tan(x)))=1-1/2!*x^2-11/4!*x^4-301/6!*x^6-16631/8!*x^8...
formula: a(n)=-(2*sum(k=1..2*n, (C(k-1)*sum(j=2*k..2*n, binomial(j-1,2*k-1)*j!*2^(2*n-j-2*k)*(-1)^((n+k)+j)*stirling2(2*n,j))))) with n>0, a(0)=1, C(n)=A000108(n) (Catalan numbers). [_Vladimir Kruchinin_, Oct 08 2012]

A012085.name: Even coefficients in expansion of cos(x)/sqrt(cos(2*x)).

A012091.name: cos(arcsin(arctan(x)))=1-1/2!*x^2+5/4!*x^4-109/6!*x^6+4521/8!*x^8...
formula: a(n) = (2*n)!*sum(k=1..2*n, ((2*k)!*binomial(2*k-2,k-1)*(-1)^(n+k+1)*sum(i=2*k..2*n, (2^(i+1)*stirling1(i,2*k)*binomial(2*n-1,i-1))/i!))/(k*2^(4*k))) with n>0, a(0)=1. [_Vladimir Kruchinin_, Oct 08 2012]

A012101.name: Expansion of tan(arcsin(sinh(x))) (odd powers only).
formula: E.g.f.: sinh(x) / sqrt(1 - sinh(x)^2). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 06 2015

A012103.name: cos(arcsin(sinh(x))) = 1-1/2!*x^2-7/4!*x^4-121/6!*x^6-5167/8!*x^8...
formula: For n>0, a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} Sum_{j=0..k-1} Pochhammer(-1/2,k) * binomial(2k,j)*(-1)^j*2^(1+2n-2k)*(j-k)^(2n)/k!. - _Benedict W. J. Irwin_, May 25 2017

A012109.name: sec(arcsin(sinh(x)))=1+1/2!*x^2+13/4!*x^4+421/6!*x^6+26713/8!*x^8...
formula: E.g.f.: Sum_{n>=0} a(n) * x^(2*n) / (2*n)! = sec(arcsin(sinh(x))) = 1 / sqrt(1 - sinh(x)^2).
E.g.f.: Sum_{n>=0} a(n) * x^(2*n+1) / (2*n+1)! = F(i x| -1) / i where F(phi|m) is the elliptic integral of the 1st kind.

A012113.name: Expansion of e.g.f. tan(arcsin(arcsinh(x))) (odd powers only).

A012114.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arctan(arcsin(arcsinh(x))), odd powers only.

A012115.name: Expansion of e.g.f. of cos(arcsin(arcsinh(x))), even powers only.

A012123.name: E.g.f.: exp(arcsin(tanh(x))).
formula: a(n) = (-i)^n * Z(n,i), where i = sqrt(-1) and Z(n,x) denotes the n-th zigzag polynomial as described in A147309. Alternative form of the egf: {sec(i*x) - tan(i*x)}^i. - _Peter Bala_, Jan 26 2011

a(n)=sum(m=1..n, sum(r=m..n, (sum(k=r..n, (-1)^((3*k)/2)*(sum(i=0..k, (2^i*stirling1(m+i,m)* binomial(m+k-1,m+i-1))/(m+i)!))*binomial((r-2)/2,(r-m-k)/2)))*((-1)^(r-m)+1)*sum(k=0..r-m, binomial(k-1,r-1)*k!*2^(n-k)*stirling2(n,k)*(-1)^(r+k))))/2, n>0, a(0)=1. - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Jun 09 2011
a(n) = sum(i=0..n-1, binomial(n-1,i)*euler(i)*a(n-i-1)), a(0)=1. - _Vladimir Kruchinin_, Feb 26 2015

A012125.name: Expansion of x/ (1-4*x+16*x^2)^(3/2).
formula: a(n)= (2(2n-1)/(n-1))*a(n-1) - (16n/(n-1))*a(n-2), starting with a(0) = 0 and a(1) = 1. - C. Ronaldo (aga_new_ac(AT)hotmail.com), Dec 15 2004

A012131.name: cosh(arcsin(tanh(x)))=1+1/2!*x^2-3/4!*x^4+21/6!*x^6-263/8!*x^8...
formula: Observe that arcsin(tanh(x)) = int {0..x} 1/cosh(t) so the generating function for this sequence is cosh( int {0..x} 1/cosh(t) ). Note the similarity to the generating function for A000364: cosh( int {0..x} 1/cos(t) ) = 1+x^2/2!+5*x^4/4!+61*x^6/6!+... - Peter Bala, Aug 24 2011.

A012132.name: Numbers z such that x*(x+1) + y*(y+1) = z*(z+1) is solvable in positive integers x,y.

A012136.name: Expansion of e.g.f. tan(arcsin(arctanh(x))) (odd powers only).

A012142.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arctanh(arcsin(arctanh(x))), odd powers only.

A012150.name: exp(tan(arcsin(x))) = 1+x+1/2!*x^2+4/3!*x^3+13/4!*x^4+76/5!*x^5...
formula: E.g.f.: S(x) = exp(x/sqrt(1-x^2)) = 1 + 2*(x/sqrt(1-x^2))/(G(0) - x/sqrt(1-x^2)), G(k) = 8*k + 2 + (x^2)/((1-x^2)*(8*k+6) + x^2/G(k+1)); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Dec 16 2011

A012164.name: sinh(tan(arcsinh(x))) = x+2/3!*x^3+16/5!*x^5+216/7!*x^7+6400/9!*x^9...
formula: a(n) ~ (-1)^n * 2^(2*n+2) * n^(2*n) * cos(tanh(Pi/2)) / ((cosh(Pi)+1) * exp(2*n)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 30 2013

A012185.name: Expansion of e.g.f.: exp(arctan(sin(x)))=1+x+1/2!*x^2-2/3!*x^3-11/4!*x^4+16/5!*x^5...
formula: E.g.f.: 1 + 2*sin(x)/(Q(0)-sin(x)), where Q(k) =  4*k+2 + (sin(x))^2*(4*k^2+8*k+5)/Q(k+1) ; (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Dec 18 2013

A012200.name: arctanh(arctan(arcsin(x))) = x + 1/3!*x^3 + 17/5!*x^5 + 393/7!*x^7 + 25601/9!*x^9 + ...
formula: Conjecture: a(n) ~ (2*n)! / (sin(tan(1)))^(2*n+1). Because sin(tan(1)) = 0.9999103740052..., is not possible to verify this numerically from 1000 terms. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 07 2015

A012212.name: Number of squarefree palindromes over {0, 1, 2} of length 2n+1.

A012244.name: a(n+2) = (2n+3)*a(n+1) + (n+1)^2*a(n), a(0) = 1, a(1) = 1.
formula: a(n) = n!/2^n*A006139(n) = n!*Sum_{k=floor(n/2)..n} 2^(k-n)*C(n, k)*C(k, n-k). Sum_{n>=0} a(n)*x^n/n!^2 = exp(x)*BesselI(0, sqrt(2)*x). a(n) is the central coefficient of n!*(1+x+x^2/2)^n. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Mar 22 2004

The function B(x) := int {t=0..x} A(t), obtained by integrating the generating function A(x), satisfies the autonomous differential equation d/dx(B(x)) = 1/(cos(B(x))-sin(B(x))). Compare with A190392.
Thus B(x), and hence A(x), can be found by inverting the function int {t=0..x} (cos(t)-sin(t)). By applying [Dominici, Theorem 4.1] the result can be expressed as

A(x) = 1 + sum {n>=1} D^n[1/(cos(t)-sin(t))](0)*x^n/n!, where the nested derivative D^n[f](x) of a function f(x) is defined recursively as D^0[f](x) = 1 and D^(n+1)[f](x) = d/dx(f(x)*D^n[f](x)) for n >= 0. Thus a(n) = D^n[1/(cos(t)-sin(t))](0). (End)
E.g.f. at offset 1: Series_Reversion(cos(x) + sin(x) - 1). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Aug 08 2012

A012245.name: Characteristic function of factorial numbers; also decimal expansion of Liouville's number or Liouville's constant.
formula: G.f.: Sum_{i>=1} x^Product_{j=1..i} j. - _Jon Perry_, Mar 31 2004

A012248.name: Expansion of e.g.f. exp(arcsinh(arcsin(x))).
formula: E.g.f.: Q(0)-1, where Q(k) =  2 + arcsin(x)/(1 - arcsin(x)/Q(k+1) ); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Dec 19 2013

A012249.name: Volume of a certain rational polytope whose points with given denominator count certain sets of Standard Tableaux.

A012251.name: exp(arcsinh(arctan(x)))=1+x+1/2!*x^2-2/3!*x^3-11/4!*x^4+24/5!*x^5...
formula: E.g.f.: Q(0)-1, where Q(k) =  2 + arctan(x)/(1 - arctan(x)/Q(k+1) ); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Dec 19 2013

A012252.name: exp(arcsinh(arcsinh(x))) = 1+x+1/2!*x^2-1/3!*x^3-7/4!*x^4+9/5!*x^5...
formula: a(n) ~ (-1)^(n/2+1) * 2 * sqrt(tan(1)) * n^(n-1) * exp(-n) / (sin(1))^n, if n is even and a(n) ~ (-1)^((n-1)/2) * 2 * n^(n-1)*exp(-n), if n is odd. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 30 2013

A012253.name: exp(arcsinh(tanh(x))) = 1+x+1/2!*x^2-2/3!*x^3-11/4!*x^4+16/5!*x^5...
formula: a(n) ~ n! * (-cos(n*Pi/2)) * (4/Pi)^n / n^(3/2), if n is even and a(n) ~ n! * 2 * sin(n*Pi/2) * (2/Pi)^(n+1), if n is odd. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 30 2013

A012254.name: exp(arcsinh(arctanh(x)))=1+x+1/2!*x^2+2/3!*x^3+5/4!*x^4+24/5!*x^5...
formula: E.g.f.: Q(0)-1, where Q(k) = 2 + arctanh(x)/(1 - arctanh(x)/Q(k+1) ); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Dec 19 2013

A012257.name: Irregular triangle read by rows: row 0 is {2}; if row n is {r_1, ..., r_k} then row n+1 is {r_k 1's, r_{k-1} 2's, r_{k-2} 3's, etc.}.
formula: Sum of row n = A011784(n+2); e.g. row 5 is {1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 4} and the sum of the elements is 1+1+1+2+2+3+4 = 14 = A011784(7). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 06 2003

A012259.name: E.g.f. exp(arctanh(tan(x))) = 1 + x + x^2/2! + 5*x^3/3! + 17*x^4/4! + 121*x^5/5! + ...
formula: Alternative form of e.g.f: sqrt(sec(2*x) + tan(2*x)) = 1 + x + x^2/2! + 5*x^3/3! + 17*x^4/4! + ... (where sec(x)=1/cos(x)). - _Peter Bala_, Jan 11 2011
a(n) = 2^n*Z(n,1/2), where Z(n,x) is the n-th zigzag polynomial as defined in A147309.

Put y = x*log(x)/4. The connection between the expansion sqrt(2/(1+x^x)) = 1 - y - y^2/2! + 5*y^3/3! + 17*y^4/4! - 121*y^5/5! ... and the present sequence is explained in the answer to Math StackExchange Question 6939. - _Peter Bala_, Jul 10 2011
exp(arctanh(tan(x))) = sqrt( (1 + tan(x))/(1 - tan(x) ) ) = sqrt( tan(x+pi/4) ). - _David Callan_, Dec 13 2011
E.g.f. A(x) satisfies: A(x) = exp( Integral (A(x)^2 + A(-x)^2)/2 dx ). - _Paul D. Hanna_, Feb 04 2017
E.g.f. A(x) satisfies: A'(x) = A(x) * (A(x)^2 + A(-x)^2)/2. - _Paul D. Hanna_, Feb 04 2017

A012264.name: Number of real roots of x - x^3/3! + x^5/5! - ... + (-1)^n*x^(2n+1)/(2n+1)!.

A012269.name: Expansion of e.g.f.: arctan(log(x+1)*log(x+1)).
formula: a(n) ~ (n-1)! * (-1)^(n+1) * sin(n*arctan(sin(1/sqrt(2)) / (cos(1/sqrt(2)) - exp(1/sqrt(2))))) * (exp(1/sqrt(2)) / sqrt(1 + exp(sqrt(2)) - 2*exp(1/sqrt(2)) * cos(1/sqrt(2))))^n. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jan 02 2014

A012271.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arcsinh(log(x+1)*log(x+1)).
formula: Lim sup n->infinity (|a(n)|/n!)^(1/n) = 1.4236247666... = exp(1/sqrt(2))/sqrt(1+exp(sqrt(2)) - 2*exp(1/sqrt(2))*cos(1/sqrt(2))). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 02 2013

A012274.name: Expansion of e.g.f.: sech(log(x+1)*log(x+1)).
formula: Lim sup n->infinity |a(n)/n!|^(1/n) = exp(sqrt(Pi)/4) / sqrt(2*(cosh(sqrt(Pi)/2) - cos(sqrt(Pi)/2))) = 1.24168087005499040594... . - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Dec 10 2015

A012278.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arctanh(exp(x)*log(x+1)).
formula: a(n) ~ (n-1)! / (2*(exp(r)-1)^n), where r = 0.5122224330332299... is the root of the equation r*exp(exp(r)-1)=1. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 24 2013

A012285.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arcsinh(sin(x)*log(x+1)).
formula: Lim sup n->infinity (|a(n)|/n!)^(1/n) = 1.144501665199369... = abs(1/r), where r is the complex root of the equation 1+r = exp(-I/sin(r)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 02 2013

A012287.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arctanh(sin(x)*log(x+1))=2/2!*x^2-3/3!*x^3+4/4!*x^4-20/5!*x^5...
formula: a(n) ~ (n-1)! * (-1)^n / (2 * r^n), where r = 0.7642695126688585683463... is the root of the equation log(1-r)*sin(r) = -1. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 05 2015

A012292.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arctanh(sin(x)*exp(x)) = x+2/2!*x^2+4/3!*x^3+24/4!*x^4+180/5!*x^5...
formula: a(n) ~ 1/2 * (n-1)! / r^n, where r = 0.588532743981861... is the real root of the equation sin(r) = exp(-r). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 25 2013

A012297.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arctan(sin(x)*sin(x)), even powers only.

A012299.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arcsinh(sin(x)*sin(x)), even indexed terms only.

A012301.name: Expansion of e.g.f. arctanh(sin(x)*sin(x)), even powers only.

A012302.name: Expansion of e.g.f. sec(sin(x)*sin(x)), even powers only.

A012303.name: Expansion of e.g.f. sech(sin(x)*sin(x)), even powers only.

A012318.name: tan(arcsin(x)*exp(x))=x+2/2!*x^2+6/3!*x^3+32/4!*x^4+240/5!*x^5...
formula: a(n) ~ n! / ((Pi/2 + exp(r)/sqrt(1-r^2)) * r^(n+1)), where r = 0.70212550839123612037106419625287862875439228120419... is the root of the equation arcsin(r)*exp(r) = Pi/2. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 06 2015

A012324.name: arctanh(arcsin(x)*exp(x))=x+2/2!*x^2+6/3!*x^3+32/4!*x^4+248/5!*x^5...
formula: a(n) ~ (n-1)! / (2 * r^n), where r = 0.546947494527286418832891321710111770819... is the root of the equation arcsin(r)*exp(r) = 1. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 05 2015

A012330.name: tan(arcsin(x)*sin(x))=2/2!*x^2+280/6!*x^6+1344/8!*x^8+770848/10!*x^10...
formula: a(n) ~ c * (2*n)! / n^(3/2), where c = sin(1)/(sqrt(Pi)*(1 + cos(Pi*sin(1)))) = 3.9081600321945... . - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 29 2016

A012340.name: exp(arcsin(x)*arcsin(x))=1+2/2!*x^2+20/4!*x^4+488/6!*x^6+22416/8!*x^8...
formula: a(n) ~ exp(Pi^2/4) * sqrt(Pi) * (2*n-1)! / sqrt(n). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 08 2015

A012345.name: Coefficients in the expansion sinh(arcsin(x)*arcsin(x)) = 2*x^2/2!+8*x^4/4!+248*x^6/6!+11328*x^8/8!+...
formula: a(n) ~ sqrt(Pi) * cosh(Pi^2/4) * (2*n)! / (2 * n^(3/2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 08 2015

A012349.name: cosh(arcsin(x)*arcsin(x))=1+12/4!*x^4+240/6!*x^6+11088/8!*x^8...
formula: a(n) ~ sqrt(Pi) * sinh(Pi^2/4) * (2*n)! / (2 * n^(3/2)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 08 2015

A012363.name: arctanh(tan(x)*exp(x))=x+2/2!*x^2+7/3!*x^3+36/4!*x^4+285/5!*x^5...

formula: a(n) = (2^(2*k)) * (2^(2*k)-1) * B(2*k) / k with k = 2*n+1, where Bernoulli numbers B(2*k) = A027641(2*k) / A027642(2*k). That this gives integers follows from von Staudt's theorem. - _Frank Ellermann_, May 14 2001
E.g.f.: sec(x)^2 + sech(x)^2 = Sum_{k>=0} a(k) x^(4k) / (4k)!. - _Michael Somos_, Mar 06 2004
E.g.f.: log(cosh(x) / cos(x)) = Sum_{k>=0} a(k) x^(4k+2) / (4k+2)!. - _Michael Somos_, Feb 05 2011
a(n) = A001250(4*n) if n>0. - _Michael Somos_, Feb 05 2011
